The paper deals with the problem of learning an unknown distribution over a set of $n$-bit strings under the deletion channel noise model. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT), as well as to data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM, cs.CC) for population recovery. The paper also uses techniques from machine learning (cs.LG) to obtain sample complexity upper bounds.
